stupidchess-uwsgi (17.1015.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Merge branch 'release/17.1015.0'
  * Fixed a last issue with the nginx config to serve _version.json
  * Including the templates in the build now
  * Fixed deploy setting to deploy to my dockerhub repo
  * Updated mongo chart dependency and deployment
  * [RELEASE] Bumping versions to release version 17.1015.0
  * Adding a way to access mongo from a nodeport
  * Documentation done
  * Updated to a new version of jscripts and made some changes so they work. Added most of the necessary readmes, but I still need to write the big main one
  * Added a bash script for setting up a stupidchess game without having to start a uwsgi container or exec into one
  * Added configuration to read in the database password for mongo, also added a bunch of READMEs that I need to fill out before releaseing
  * Fixed a small issue with the updating select component
  * Added how-to-play page to teach people the wonderful game of stupidchess. Also fixed the issue with highlighted squares for the other player and both colors showing up in board setup select for two player games
  * Big refactor of my service and database code   - Added daos to handle direct interactions with the DB   - Adapted the existing services to work with daos instead of the mongoengine models directly   - Adapted the existing services to work with daos instead of the mongoengine models directly
  * Highlighting pieces that need to be placed in board setup mode now, as well as changed the shapes of the piece select grids
  * Fixed a couple remaining bugs with the checker, checker kings can move twice on their first move I've decided as well.
  * Cleaned up the UI a bit. The footer sticks to the bottom now. Added a homepage as well
  * Added pawn promotion, only a homepage away from releasing the next version
  * Added a move list on the game page so you can look at the list of the last few moves that have occurred. Required some new APIs and refactoring of the paged table stuff
  * Added an API to retrieve moves, which required a bit of refactoring of the game and move services
  * Cleaned up a bunch of js imports and exports, and also fixed a couple of small remaining bugs in how we were showing game results
  * Added proper error handling on all API calls, displaying an error message when one fails
  * Added kinging checkers, refactoring the move_application_service a bit in the process, also added a help text element on the game screen to explain to people how to play because the UX is so bad
  * Using the React table for the player records now as well
  * Cleaned up UI a bit
  * Added new themes! There's a christmas and a michigan theme now
  * Gzipping all of my frontend assets now, and also added the module hoisting plugin for webpack, made my frontend code MUCH smaller
  * Added color on active games when it's your turn to move, also added a new eslint rule to check for semicolons and added a ton of semicolons that were missing
  * Added pagination on game lists on the profile page
  * Added a create game button on the profile and finally fixed the stupid checker issue
  * A lot more done   - Added authorization on possible moves and apply moves so only the user who controls a color in a game can get a list of possible moves or apply a move   - Updated lists on profile pages to only show games that a user is involved in   - Cleaned up imports to use only relative imports   - Fixed one checker bug, but there's still another issue
  * Finished fairly large refactor   - All pages rendered server side now   - Added error messages when either a profile or game page is retrieved with an invalid uuid   - Got redirecting on login working properly   - Cleaned up how our select elements work in a few places   - Creating games with a form now, and doing proper form validation on the request
  * Massive refactor   - Rendering templates with flask now, which enables me to not have to request the current user information on every page load   - Also refactored the forms to have server-side validation, and have them rendered partially server-side, using wtforms   - Also made a couple chnages to the record service   - Changed up a few links as well. Getting rid of the '.html' suffix on all of my pages
  * Added a change password page, tried to get rememberme working, but still having issues. Got better player record metrics set up using aggregations
  * Cleaned up the setup script a bit and added logging to it. Changed the moves API to return the moves that it creates
  * Made uuid links fixed-width
  * [RELEASE] Bumping versions to next development version 17.0920.0-dev

